	<h2>Student Internship Selection Criteria</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>Students must be working toward a master's degree or higher in counseling, social work or other related field, at an accredited university.</li>
		<li>Students from CACREP approved programs and APA accredited programs will be given preference.</li>
		<li>Students should have completed practicum, and also coursework in counseling theories, ethics, multicultural counseling and group counseling prior to beginning internship.</li>
		<li>Students with play therapy training/experience will be given preference.</li>
		<li>Bilingual candidates will be given preference.</li>
		<li>Students must pass criminal and CPS background checks.</li>
	</ol>

	<h2>Student Internship Requirements</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>Students must commit to 2 semesters at Scotty's House CAC.  For those on alternative schedules, we request a minimum commitment of 26 weeks.</li>
		<li>Students are required to spend at least 10 to 15 hours per week at Scotty's House CAC during their internship.</li>
